title: TU Power Poll: Trinity stays No. 1; two new teams move in
text:
TU Power Poll: Trinity stays No. 1; two new teams move in 
By Justin Barney Thu, Oct 22, 2015 @ 9:21 pm | updated Thu, Oct 22, 2015 @ 11:24 pm Photos Perry Knotts, For the St. Augustine Record Ponte Vedra's Jarrett Stepp (84) stiff arms Bartram Trail linebacker Nicos Rivera during a game on Oct. 9. 
POWER POLL 
Last week’s rankings in parentheses. All games 7 p.m. Friday unless indicated 
1. (1) TRINITY CHRISTIAN (8-0), CLASS 3A 
Last week: d. Duval Charter, 51-6 
Thursday’s game: d. Tallahassee Lincoln, 49-18 
Glance: The Conquerors have just one major obstacle left for an unbeaten regular season — Pensacola Pine Forest on Nov. 6 
2. (2) RAINES (7-0), CLASS 4A 
Last week: d. Jackson, 56-0 
This week: at West Nassau (5-2) 
Glance: The Vikings can officially wrap up a state playoff berth with a victory over the Warriors. Then all attention shifts toward Bolles (Oct. 29). 
3. (3) COLUMBIA (6-1), CLASS 7A 
Last week: d. Atlantic Coast, 27-16 
This week: at Fletcher (5-2) 
Glance: The Tigers have traditionally had one rough district outing a season under coach Brian Allen. Could that have come last week against the Stingrays? 
4. (4) ST. AUGUSTINE (7-0), CLASS 6A 
Last week: d. White, 31-14 
This week: at Nease (5-2) 
Glance: The Yellow Jackets are zoning in on another district championship, their 12th consecutive, which they’ll clinch with a win over the Panthers. 
5. (5) BOLLES (7-1), CLASS 4A 
Last week: d. Port Orange Atlantic, 42-0 
This week: at Fernandina Beach (2-6) 
Glance: As is the case with Raines, the Bulldogs are in the state playoffs with a win this week. 
6. (6) MANDARIN (7-0), CLASS 8A 
Last week: d. Sandalwood, 52-29 
This week: Spruce Creek (4-3) 
Glance: That 31-point third quarter against Sandalwood last week will go down in history at Mandarin. The Mustangs will clinch the 1-8A title with a win. 
7. (7) UNIVERSITY CHRISTIAN (6-1), CLASS 2A 
Last week: d. Cedar Creek Christian, 61-18 
This week: at Brentwood Academy, Tenn. (7-1) 
Glance: With the 2-2A title clinched, UC heads to Tennessee for a major challenge in the Eagles, a team MaxPreps ranks No. 2 in the state. 
8. (8) OAKLEAF (6-1), CLASS 7A 
Last week : d. Arlington CD, 42-8 
This week: Creekside (0-7) 
Glance: The Knights are positioned for a winner-takes-a-playoff-berth game at Bartram Trail next week and can’t afford a slip up here. 
9. (NR) PONTE VEDRA (6-2), CLASS 5A 
Last week : d. Bishop Kenny, 36-7 
This week: Off 
Glance: The Sharks are in the playoffs, and can clinch the 4-5A title with a Parker loss to Bishop Kenny this week. 
10. (NR) FORT WHITE (5-2), CLASS 1A 
Last week : d. Union County, 44-41 
This week: Gainesville Eastside (1-6), 7:30 
Glance: The Indians moved into the poll after a big win over state-ranked Union. Fort White has played very well this season, with its lone losses to University Christian and Suwannee. 

Dropped out: Sandalwood (6-2, lost to Mandarin, 52-29); Union County (6-1, lost to Fort White 44-41).
